es-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwho-are-the-first-13-israeli-hostages-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Freed%20from%20captivity%3A%20The%20Israeli%20hostages%20released%20by%20Hamas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700830260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F70x70%2Fskynews-israel-hostages-released_6370983.jpg%3F20231124172841%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-we-know-about-the-israeli-hostages-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thirteen%20Israeli%20hostages%20have%20been%20released%20by%20Hamas%20after%20being%20held%20for%20almost%20seven%20weeks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A44%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-we-know-about-the-israeli-hostages-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-we-know-about-the-israeli-hostages-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-we-know-about-the-israeli-hostages-released-by-hamas-13015007%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20Largest%20Iceberg%2C%20About%20The%20Size%20Of%20Dubai%2C%20Moves%20After%2030%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20stuck%20to%20the%20ocean%20floor%20for%20over%2030%20years%2C%20the%20world's%20biggest%20iceberg%2C%20A-23a%2C%20is%20finally%20on%20the%20move!%20The%20iceberg%2C%20which%20broke%20off%20from%20the%20Antarctic%20coastline%20in%201986%2C%20had%20been%20grounded%20in%20the%20Weddell%20Sea%2C%20but%20it%20has%20now%20broken%20free%20and%20is%20drifting%20towards%20warmer%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20iceberg%20has%20an%20area%20of%204%2C000%20sq%20km%2C%20which%20is%20close%20to%20that%20of%20the%20emirate%20of%20Dubai%2C%20which%20is%20spread%20across%204%2C114%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Andrew%20Fleming%2C%20a%20remote%20sensing%20expert%20from%20the%20British%20Antarctic%20Survey%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-67507558%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20asked%20a%20couple%20of%20colleagues%20about%20this%2C%20wondering%20if%20there%20was%20any%20possible%20change%20in%20shelf%20water%20temperatures%20that%20might%20have%20provoked%20it%2C%20but%20the%20consensus%20is%20the%20time%20has%20just%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20grounded%20since%201986%20but%20eventually%20it%20was%20going%20to%20decrease%20(in%20size)%20sufficiently%20to%20lose%20grip%20and%20start%20moving.%20I%20spotted%20first%20movement%20back%20in%202020.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.guinnessworldrecords.com%2Fworld-records%2F81727-largest-iceberg%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGuniness%20World%20Record%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20unlike%20many%20of%20the%20large%20icebergs%20that%20detach%20from%20Antarctica%20and%20float%20away%2C%20A23A%20has%20only%20moved%20a%20few%20hundred%20kilometres%20since%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bborn%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20Filchner%20Ice%20Shelf%20in%20August%201986.%20This%20is%20because%20it%20is%20grounded%20(stuck)%20on%20the%20sea%20floor%20and%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20is%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20fragmenting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EGWR%3C%2Fem%3E%20further%20stated%20that%20the%20record%20for%20the%20largest%20current%20iceberg%20changes%20hands%20most%20years%2C%20as%20new%20icebergs%20are%20calved%20off%20the%20Antarctic%20continent%20and%20subsequently%20break%20into%20smaller%20fragments.%20The%20former%20record%20holder%20was%20A76%2C%20which%20detached%20from%20the%20Ronne%20Ice%20Shelf%20in%20the%20Weddell%20Sea%20in%20May%202021%20but%20has%20since%20fragmented%20into%20three%20pieces.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20new%20record%20passes%20back%20to%20A23A.%3C%