Frest-of-world%2Firish-police-arrest-34-people-in-dublin-rioting-following-stabbings-outside-a-school%2Famp_articleshow%2F105473264.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Firish-police-arrest-34-people-in-dublin-rioting-following-stabbings-outside-a-school%2Famp_articleshow%2F105473264.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Governors%20Cannot%20Keep%20Bills%20Pending%20Indefinitely%3A%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13130248%2FSupreme-Court-p.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Governors%20are%20not%20empowered%20to%20keep%20a%20Bill%20pending%20indefinitely%20without%20any%20action%20whatsoever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F44896%2F44896_2023_1_19_48220_Judgement_10-Nov-2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%20empowers%20governors%20to%20either%20give%20assent%20to%20passed%20Bills%2C%20withhold%20assent%2C%20or%20reserve%20them%20for%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20consideration%20when%20he%20or%20she%20receives%20a%20Bill%20from%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20highlighted%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Csubstantive%20part%20of%20Article%20200%20empowers%20the%20governor%20to%20withhold%20assent%20to%20the%20Bill%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20in%20such%20an%20event%2C%20the%20governor%20must%20communicate%20it%20to%20the%20State%20Legislature%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D%2C%20warranting%20the%20reconsideration%20of%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20expression%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D%20is%20significant.%20It%20conveys%20a%20constitutional%20imperative%20of%20expedition.%20Failure%20to%20take%20a%20call%20and%20keeping%20a%20Bill%20duly%20passed%20for%20indeterminate%20periods%20is%20a%20course%20of%20action%20inconsistent%20with%20that%20expression.%20Constitutional%20language%20is%20not%20surplusage%2C%E2%80%9D%20its%20judgment%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%20that%20failing%20to%20read%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20power%20in%20Article%20200%20in%20this%20manner%20would%20put%20him%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cposition%20to%20virtually%20veto%E2%80%9D%20the%20elected%20legislature%E2%80%99s%20functioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20a%20course%20of%20action%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20%5Bthe%5D%20fundamental%20principles%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%20based%20on%20a%20parliamentary%20pattern%20of%20governance%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20governors%20are%20required%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdeclare%E2%80%9D%20which%20option%20they%20choose%20to%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20remarks%20were%20made%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20three-judge%20bench%2C%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fsc-talks-tough-on-punjab-tn-governors-sitting-over-bills-says-dont-play-with-fire%2F1840999%2F%5C%22%3ENovember%2010%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20based%20on%20a%20plea%20by%20the%20Punjab%20government%20against%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit.%20The%20governor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-inaction-bills-supreme-court-punjab%5C%22%3Ehad%20kept%3C%2Fa%3E%20seven%20Bills%2C%20sent%20to%20him%20by%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%E2%80%99s%20detailed%20judgment%20was%20made%20public%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-as-ruling-partys-storm-troopers%5C%22%3EGovernors%20as%20Ruling%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Storm%20Troopers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%20for%20other%