sition%20of%20being%20a%20former%20JNU%20student%20union%20president%20or%20as%20a%20student%20activist%20whom%20you%20sat%20with%20for%20long%20hours%20debating%2C%20nor%20as%20a%20friend%20who%20has%20several%20pleasant%20memories%20of%20working%20with%20you.%20I%20am%20saying%20this%20from%20a%20moral%2C%20ethical%2C%20and%20political%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20your%20interview%20to%20ANI%2C%20you%20claimed%20that%20you%20had%20this%20sudden%20change%20of%20heart%20after%20seeing%20the%20great%20service%20of%20Modi%20and%20Shah.%20But%20strangely%2C%20you%20conveniently%20remained%20silent%20on%20the%20series%20of%20changes%20of%20heart%20you%20have%20had%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20I%20think%20you%20should%20also%20enlighten%20why%20you%20floated%20a%20party%20only%20to%20dissolve%20it%20later%2C%20and%20why%20you%20decided%20to%20file%20a%20petition%20against%20the%20dilution%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20only%20to%20have%20another%20change%20of%20heart%20and%20withdraw%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yes%2C%20I%20feel%20disappointed.%20Let%20me%20explain%20why%20I%20feel%20this%20way.%20My%20friend%20Umar%20Khalid%20is%20languishing%20in%20jail.%20Similarly%2C%20many%20Kashmiri%20journalists%2C%20human%20rights%20activists%2C%20and%20other%20innocent%20people%20are%20in%20jails%20without%20any%20trial%20and%20under%20trumped%20up%20charges%20of%20UAPA.%20Father%20Stan%20Swamy%20passed%20away%20in%20jail%20facing%20a%20false%20and%20politically%20motivated%20case%20in%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20matter%20and%20was%20not%20even%20provided%20with%20a%20straw%20to%20eat%20food.%20Fatima%20Nafees%20is%20still%20fighting%20to%20find%20her%20son.%20Radhika%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eamma%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20still%20battling%20all%20odds%20to%20get%20justice%20for%20Rohith%20Vemula.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20surprises%20me%20is%20that%20you%20were%20part%20of%20all%20these%20movements.%20Not%20only%20these%20but%20many%20more.%20It%20is%20this%20heartlessness%20where%20I%20wish%20to%20draw%20a%20line.%20The%20way%20you%20whitewashed%20the%20crimes%20of%20Modi%20and%20Shah%20by%20praising%20them%20for%20being%20%E2%80%9Cselfless%E2%80%9D%20cannot%20just%20be%20a%20change%20of%20heart.%20For%20their%20histories%20to%20be%20forgiven%20and%20forgotten%2C%20for%20which%20there%20has%20never%20been%20remorse%2C%20requires%20not%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20but%20maybe%20an%20absence%20of%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20who%20faced%20witch%20hunts%2C%20unable%20to%20fight%20for%20whatever%20reasons%2C%20either%20became%20silent%2C%20left%20the%20country%20or%20figured%20out%20a%20way%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20political%20path.%20Yet%2C%20they%20did%20not%20turn%20into%20supporters%20of%20what%20is%20a%20palpably%20fascist%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20podcast%2C%20you%20spoke%20about%20a%20flirtation%20with%20revolutionary%20politics%20in%20your%2020s.%20Well%2C%20what%20made%20journalist%20Smita%20Prakash%20sit%20with%20you%20and%20give%20value%20to%20your%20opinions%20is%20this%20very%20flirtation%20with%20revolutionary%20politics%20and%20the%20sacrifices%20of%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20students%20on%20which%20it%20is%20founded.%20Remember%20that%20Bhagat%20Singh%20was%20in%20his%2020s%20when%20he%20was%20martyred%20fighting%20for%20the%20nation.%20There%20are%20hundreds%20of%20such%20examples%20in%20our%20freedom%20movement%2C%20post-independence%2C%20and%20from%20the%20campus%20you%20graduated.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20tell%20you%20the%20story%20of%20Chandrashekar%20Prasad%2C%20twice-elected%20JNUSU%20President%20who%20was%20killed%20by%20feudal%20goons%20for%20fighting%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20landless%20people.%20By%20the%20way%2C%20he%20was%20in%20his%2020s%20too.%20It%20is%20the%20cynical%20and%20corrupted%20who%20find%20the%20revolutionary%20zeal%20of%20those%20in%20their%2020s%20mere%20%E2%80%98idealistic%E2%80%99.%20To%20dismiss%20the%20honesty%20of%20this%20spirit%2C%20as%20you%20have%20done%2C%20is%20to%20demean%20and%20insult%20the%20struggles%20and%20movements%20of%20students%20in%20universities%2C%20the%20very%20movements%20that%20have%20contributed%20to%20your%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20you%20term%20your%20interactions%20and%20time%20with%20many%20of%20us%20as%20%E2%80%98being%20in%20an%20echo%20chamber%E2%80%99%20only%20made%20me%20question%20my%20own%20earlier%20appreciation%20of%20your%20intelligence%2C%20political%20acumen%2C%20and%20nuanced%20articulations.%20Again%2C%20let%20me%20remind%20you%2C%20that%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98echo%20chamber%E2%80%99%20helped%20you%20shape%20your%20opinions%20and%20positions%20which%20the%20people%20resisting%20fascism%20welcomed%20with%20open%20hearts.%20Now%20to%20turn%20around%20and%20be%20dismissive%20only%20shows%20you%20are%20capable%20of%20disowning%20anything%2C%20if%20need%20be.%20What%20guarantee%20is%20it%20that%20once%20the%20current%20regime%20is%20defeated%2C%20you%20won%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20again%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20this%20zeal%20is%20not%20restricted%20to%20the%2020s.%20May%20I%20remind%20you%20that%20Father%20Stan%20Swamy%20was%20not%20in%20his%2020s%2C%20nor%20are%20Fatima%20Nafees%20(Najeeb%E2%80%99s%20mother)%2C%20Radhika%20Amma%20(Rohith%E2%80%99s%20Mother)%2C%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20(%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0editor)%2C%20Paranjoy%20Guha%20Thakurta%2C%20and%20many%20others%20who%20are%20fighting%20for%20justice%20and%20are%20hounded%20for%20exposing%20crony%20capitalism%20of%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlease%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20face%20the%20reality%20that%20your%20past%20association%20with%20left%20and%20progressive%20movements%20may%20be%20coming%20in%20the%20way%20of%20your%20future%20aspirations%2C%20and%20that%20you%20need%20to%20part%20ways%20%E2%80%93%20which%20you%20actually%20did%20a%20long%20time%20ago.%20We%20understood%20and%20never%20pointed%20fingers.%20However%2C%20if%20your%20compulsions%20or%20aspirations%20require%20insulting%20those%20very%20movements%2C%20then%20difficult%20questions%20will%20be%20asked%20about%20your%20change%20of%20heart.%20Is%20it%20really%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20or%20a%20change%20of%20direction%20in%20which%20the%20heart%20wishes%20to%20see%20some%20things%20and%20also%20%E2%80%98unsee%E2%80%99%20much%20more%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20these%20twisted%20ethical%20and%20political%20positions%20that%20are%20enabling%20fundamentalists%20to%20destroy%20India%20that%20I%20find%20difficult%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with.%20Many%20people%20have%20written%20and%20are%20saying%20that%20there%20must%20be%20some%20compulsions%20and%20pressures%20on%20you%20to%20take%20this%20drastic%20step.%20Well%2C%20if%20a%20common%20citizen%2C%20who%20is%20just%20going%20about%20their%20life%20who%20is%20facing%20the%20music%20of%20unemployment%2C%20harassment%2C%20price%20rise%2C%20and%20others%20is%20still%20resisting%2C%20voting%2C%20and%20fighting%20to%20keep%20BJP%20away%2C%20a%20lot%20is%20expected%20from%20people%20like%20us%20who%20have%20been%20part%20of%20the%20student%20and%20anti-fascist%20movements%20and%20have%20benefited%20from%20critical%20scholarship.%20It%20is%20here%20that%20you%20gave%20up%20and%20decided%20to%20turn%20sides.%20It%20is%20disheartening%20but%20not%20demotivating%2C%20as%20there%20are%20millions%20still%20resisting%20the%20BJP%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20present%20times%2C%20as%20a%20young%20research%20scholar%2C%20one%20just%20has%20to%20go%20to%20a%20job%20interview%20at%20Delhi%20University%20to%20see%20the%20consequences%20of%20commitment%20to%20a%20secular%2C%20socialist%2C%20democratic%2C%20and%20egalitarian%20nation.%20People%20are%20risking%20their%20careers%2C%20taking%20positions%20they%20are%20over-qualified%20for%20just%20because%20they%20opposed%20the%20ABVP.%20Yet%2C%20they%20are%20standing%20strong%20and%20refusing%20to%20give%20in%20to%20get%20a%20job.%20These%20are%20inspiring%20people%20to%20me%3B%20I%20find%20motivation%20to%20strive%20more%20and%20be%20upright%20in%20what%20we%20do%20in%20life.%20I%20find%20inspiration%20in%20people%20who%20refuse%20to%20strike%20bargains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20am%20not%20in%20my%2020s%20anymore%2C%20so%20please%20ignore%20my%20opinion%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EN.%20Sai%20Balaji%20is%20a%20former%20president%20of%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20Students%E2%80%99%20Union%20(JNUSU).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700800210000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F06164543%2FIMG_20190705_124249_524-e1566475547700.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fheartlessness-is-systemic-and-dangerous-a-letter-to-shehla-rashid%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20people%20who%20faced%20witch%20hunts%2C%20unable%20to%20fight%20for%20whatever%20reasons%2C%20either%20became%20silent%2C%20left%20the%20country%20or%20figured%20out%20a%20way%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20political%20path.%20Yet%2C%20they%20did%20not%20turn%20into%20supporters%20of%20what%20is%20a%20palpably%20fascist%20front.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A94%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fheartlessness-is-systemic-and-dangerous-a-letter-to-shehla-rashid%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20New%20Pathogen%2C%20WHO's%20Line%2C%20Why%20China%3F%3A%20What%20We%20Know%20About%20the%20'Unknown%20Pneumonia'%20Outbreak%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24092504%2F6838768118_4231c20017_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Amid%20an%20ongoing%20and%20fresh%20outbreak%20of%20what%20has%20emerged%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunknown%20pneumonia%E2%80%9D%20in%20China%20leading%20to%20crowding%20at%20healthcare%20facilities%20in%20northern%20China%2C%20the%20government%20of%20the%20country%20has%20ruled%20out%20the%20presence%20of%20any%20new%20or%20unknown%20pathogen.%20This%2C%20at%20least%20as%20of%20now%2C%20should%20put%20to%20rest%20fears%20of%20a%20bigger%20outbreak%20which%20could%20have%20pandemic%20potential.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuoting%20official%20conversation%20with%20Chinese%20health%20authorities%20from%20the%20Chinese%20Center%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20and%20the%20Beijing%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Hospital%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20said%20on%20November%2023%20that%20the%20upsurge%20in%20hospital%20admissions%20of%20children%20were%20due%20to%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumoniae%20%E2%80%93%20a%20bacterial%20infection%20%E2%80%93%20from%20May%3B%20and%20Respiratory%20Syncytial%20Virus%20(RSV)%2C%20adenovirus%20and%20influenza%20%E2%80%93%20all%20viral%20infections%20%E2%80%93%20from%20October%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20these%20bacterial%20and%20viral%20infections%20are%20well%20known%20and%20treatments%20to%20these%20are%20available%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20in%20case%20of%20a%20novel%20pathogen%20(a%20virus%20or%20bacteria).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20outbreak%20in%20China%20brought%20back%20eerie%20memories%20of%20the%20Sars-Cov-2%20(novel%20coronavirus)%20outbreak.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20also%20described%20as%20pneumonia%20of%20%E2%80%9Cunknown%20aetiology%20(unknown%20cause)%E2%80%9D%20in%20one%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Femergencies%2Fdisease-outbreak-news%2Fitem%2F2020-DON229%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDescription%2520of%2520the%2520Situation%2CCity%252C%2520Hubei%2520Province%2520of%2520China.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20first%20statements%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20WHO%20that%20was%20published%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20COVID-19.%20But%20now%2C%20the%20role%20of%20any%20unknown%20pathogen%20has%20been%20ruled%20out%2C%20at%20least%2C%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20while%20accepting%20the%20surge%20in%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20Chinese%20authorities%20advised%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20detection%20of%20any%20unusual%20or%20novel%20pathogens%20or%20unusual%20clinical%20presentations%2C%20including%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Liaoning%2C%20but%20only%20the%20aforementioned%20general%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%20due%20to%20multiple%20known%20pathogens%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20WHO%20has%20said%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2022%2C%20a%20day%20earlier%2C%20the%20WHO%20made%20its%20first%20formal%20statement%20regarding%20the%20outbreak%20in%20China.%20Various%20images%20circulated%20on%20social%20media%20in%20which%20hospitals%2C%20especially%20treating%20children%2C%20were%20shown%20to%20be%20overwhelmed.%20In%20the%20November%2022%20statement%2C%20the%20WHO%20had%20said%20it%20had%20sought%20more%20information%20from%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20move%20was%20necessitated%20by%20a%20report%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpromedmail.org%2Fpromed-post%2F%3Fplace%3D8713261%2C353%23promedmailmap%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProMed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%2021%20which%20spoke%20of%20undiagnosed%20pneumonia%20epidemics%20going%20on%20in%20China.%20ProMed%20is%20an%20international%20forum%20that%20identifies%20infectious%20diseases%20outbreaks%20globally%2C%20and%20is%20usually%20the%20first%20platform%20to%20alert%20the%20global%20scientific%20community%20about%20them%20%E2%80%93%20as%20it%20did%20for%20Covid-19.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20outbreak%20of%20pneumonia%20in%20China%2C%20children%E2%80%99s%20hospitals%20in%20Beijing%2C%20Liaoning%20and%20other%20places%20were%20overwhelmed%20with%20sick%20children%2C%20and%20schools%20and%20classes%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20suspension%2C%E2%80%9D%20ProMed%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20wanted%20to%20know%20whether%20there%20were%20%E2%80%9Cclusters%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9Cundiagnosed%20pneumonia%E2%80%9D%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Liaoning%20and%20if%20the%20current%20outbreak%20was%20a%20general%20pattern%20of%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Could%20be%20RSV%20or%20HMPV%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20three%20experts%20and%20all%20of%20them%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20made%20observations%20similar%20to%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20latest%20statement%20on%20the%20current%20outbreak.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20there%20are%20children%20%5Bwho%20are%20mostly%20infected%5D%2C%20it%20could%20be%20RSV%20or%20Human%20Metapneumovirus%20(HMPV)%20%E2%80%93%20both%20known%20to%20cause%20respiratory%20illness%20in%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shahid%20Jameel%2C%20a%20virologist.%20Jameel%20is%20currently%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Oxford%20University%E2%80%99s%20Green%20Templeton%20College.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERSV%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(US-CDC)%20is%20a%20common%20viral%20respiratory%20infection%20that%20usually%20causes%20mild%2C%20cold-like%20symptoms%20and%20people%20can%20recover%20in%20a%20week%20with%20or%20without%20use%20of%20antibiotics.%20However%2C%20some%20serious%20cases%20may%20require%20hospitalisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumonia%20is%20a%20bacterial%20respiratory%20system%20which%20is%20usually%20considered%20mild%20but%20serious%20cases%20be%20hospitalised.%20Both%20of%20them%20are%20transmitted%20through%20droplets%20of%20an%20infected%20person%20or%20a%20close%20contact%20with%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20RSV%20outbreaks%20elsewhere%20%5Balso%20apart%20from%20China%20%5Dafter%20good%20years%20due%20to%20quarantine%20and%20other%20restrictions%20%5Bbeing%20lifted%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jameel%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20also%20said%20something%20similar.%20%E2%80%9CSome%20of%20these%20increases%20are%20earlier%20in%20the%20season%20than%20historically%20experienced%2C%20but%20not%20unexpected%20given%20the%20lifting%20of%20COVID-19%20restrictions%2C%20as%20similarly%20experienced%20in%20other%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20explained.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmesh%20Adalja%2C%20a%20senior%20scholar%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Center%20for%20Health%20Security%2C%20says%20the%20current%20outbreak%20in%20China%20seemed%20to%20mimic%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20earlier.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20appears%20that%20this%20outbreak%20is%20likely%20the%20result%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20known%20respiratory%20pathogens%2C%20including%20Mycoplasma%20Pneumoniae%2C%20all%20attacking%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94%20similar%20to%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year%20with%20simultaneous%20outbreaks%20of%20RSV%2C%20influenza%2C%20and%20COVID-19%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20response%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20now%3F%20Why%20China%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20China%20had%20followed%20what%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Zero%20Covid%E2%80%99%20policy.%20It%20locked%20up%2C%20as%20per%20stringent%20measures%20of%20lockdown%20for%20COVID-19%2C%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20population%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20%E2%80%93%20longer%20than%20many%20other%20countries.%20This%20resulted%20in%20a%20scenario%20in%20which%20the%20population%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20exposed%20to%20other%20respiratory%20viruses%20or%20bacteria%20also%2C%20in%20the%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0And%2C%20once%20the%20measures%20were%20lifted%20this%20winter%2C%C2%A0%20this%20population%20got%20exposed%20to%20all%20of%20them%20leading%20to%20the%20surge%20in%20cases.%20Moreover%2C%20not%20getting%20exposed%20to%20these%20pathogens%20for%20a%20long%20time%20could%20also%20have%20created%20what%20is%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98immunological%20deficit%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20deficiency%20in%20natural%20immunity%20acquired%20against%20the%20pathogens%20due%20to%20exposure%20to%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharat%20Pankhania%2C%20an%20infectious%20diseases%20expert%20with%20University%20of%20Exter%20Medical%20School%2C%20UK%2C%20believes%20the%20%E2%80%98deficit%E2%80%99%20might%20not%20provide%20the%20complete%20answer%20to%20the%20ongoing%20outbreak.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CImmunological%20deficit%20is%20not%20surprising%E2%80%A6but%20then%20you%20can%20have%20more%20people%20infected%20than%20expected%20because%20of%20circumstances%20like%20crowded%20schools%2C%20crowded%20shops%2C%20buses%2C%20trains%E2%80%A6and%20there%20is%20winter%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSo%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20disentangle%20%5Bwhether%5D%20it%20is%20an%20immunological%20deficit%2C%20or%20is%20it%20environmental%20circumstances.%20Or%20perhaps%20both%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENonetheless%2C%20Pankhania%20stressed%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20patients%20responding%20to%20the%20drugs%20in%20this%20outbreak%20is%20a%20pointer%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20not%20an%20unknown%20infection.%20The%20Chinese%20authorities%2C%20per%20WHO%2C%20have%20also%20said%20there%20is%20no%20change%20in%20the%20presentation%20of%20these%20diseases%20vis-a-vis%20the%20patterns%20already%20known.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20going%20by%20the%20data%20provided%20by%20the%20Chinese%20authorities%2C%20the%20WHO%20has%20assessed%20that%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20respiratory%20illnesses%20are%20caused%20by%20the%20known%20pathogens%20which%20are%20readily%20treatable%20with%20antibiotics%2C%20if%20needed.%20And%2C%20therefore%2C%20there%20was%20no%20cause%20of%20immediate%20alarm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Pankhania%20and%20Adalja%20said%20the%20Chinese%20authorities%20must%20share%20data%20with%20the%20global%20scientific%20community.%20They%20must%C2%A0%20publish%20the%20detailed%20findings%20of%20their%20inquiry%20besides%20sharing%20genome%20sequences%20of%20the%20samples%20tested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20WHO%20has%20also%20added%20though%20information%20available%20is%20%E2%80%9Climited%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20characterise%E2%80%9D%20the%20overall%20risk%20even%20though%20winter%20season%20is%20known%20to%20create%20a%20spike%20in%20respiratory%20infections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20sounding%20a%20cautionary%20note%2C%20it%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20closely%20monitor%20the%20situation%20and%20would%20be%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20national%20authorities%20of%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700798192000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24092504%2F6838768118_4231c20017_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fchina-pneumonia-outbreak-who-pandemic%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chinese%C2%A0authorities%20told%20the%20WHO%20that%20the%20current%20outbreak%20is%C2%A0related%20to%20'already%20known'%20viruses%20or%20bacteria%2C%20thus%20ruling%20out%20any%20potential%20pandemic.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fchina-pneumonia-outbreak-who-pandemic%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20it%20Like%2C%20Growing%20up%20Muslim%20in%20Aligarh%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24082915%2F339836345_6ec5c293e6_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%20the%20novel%20%3C%2Fem%3ECity%20on%20Fire%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20coming-of-age%20memoir%20in%20which%20Zeyad%20Masroor%20Khan%20writes%2C%20with%20searing%20honesty%2C%20about%20the%20undercurrents%20of%20religious%20violence%20and%20the%20ensuing%20%E2%80%98othering%E2%80%99%20that%20followed%20him%20everywhere%20he%20went%2C%20from%20his%20schoolgoing%20days%20in%20Aligarh%2C%20through%20his%20years%20as%20a%20college%20student%20in%20Delhi%2C%20to%20ultimately%20becoming%20a%20journalist%20documenting%20history%20of%20his%20country%20as%20it%20happened.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Perhaps%20home%20is%20not%20a%20place%20but%20simply%20an%20irrevocable%20condition.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%93%20James%20Arthur%20Baldwin%2C%201924%E2%80%931987%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20slope%20was%20red%20with%20bricks%20and%20blood.%20More%20bricks%20dropped%20from%20the%20sky%20like%20missiles.%20Once%20in%20a%20while%2C%20a%20bottle%20of%20acid%20or%20a%20petrol%20bomb%20made%20its%20presence%20felt%20among%20the%20variety%20of%20objects%20being%20hurled.%20Amid%20the%20clash%20of%20religious%20slogans%20and%20verbal%20abuses%2C%20gunshots%20were%20heard.%20The%20riot%20was%20at%20its%20zenith%20%E2%80%93%20and%20my%20home%20lay%20exactly%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnger%20rose%20in%20the%20hearts%20of%20men%20flooding%20the%20streets.%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHar%20har%20Mahadev!%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20they%20shouted%20from%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20slope.%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAllahu%20Akbar!%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20shouted%20other%20angry%20men%20from%20the%20top%20of%20the%20slope.%20The%20body%20of%20a%20twenty-year-old%20boy%20lay%20somewhere%20between%20this%20mass%20of%20angry%20men%2C%20his%20intestines%20ripped%20out%2C%20his%20blood%20spreading%20across%20the%20tarmac.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20406px)%2085vw%2C%20406px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23142829%2Fimage-1530.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22406%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23142829%2Fimage-1530.png%20468w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23142829%2Fimage-1530-191x300.png%20191w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686065%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22638%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECity%20on%20Fire%2C%20Zeyad%20Masroor%20Khan%2C%20HarperCollins%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20memory%20that%20haunts%20me%20the%20most%20is%20the%20sound%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20screams%20coming%20from%20all%20directions%20at%20once.%20As%20if%20all%20the%20women%20in%20my%20mohalla%20were%20screaming%20in%20unison.%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EYa%20Allah!%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20cried%20an%20old%20woman%20standing%20in%20a%20balcony%20in%20front%20of%20the%20foyer%20of%20my%20house%2C%20wiping%20tears%20with%20her%20dupatta.%20Her%20daughter%20called%20out%20to%20her%20brother%20urgently%2C%20repeatedly.%20%E2%80%98Faisal!%20Faisal!%20Come%20back!%E2%80%99%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I%20had%20noticed%20these%20particular%20neighbours.%20The%20woman%20started%20breaking%20away%20loose%20bricks%20from%20her%20balcony%20wall%20and%20dropping%20them%20out%20to%20Faisal.%20%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20give%20them%20an%20inch%20or%20they%E2%80%99ll%20enter%20our%20homes!%E2%80%99%20she%20cried.%20Almost%20everyone%20picks%20a%20side%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20staying%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20shortage%20of%20bricks%20on%20our%20side%20of%20the%20fight.%20An%20unlucky%20neighbour%20had%20ordered%20a%20truckful%20a%20few%20days%20ago.%20Nobody%20asked%20his%20permission%20before%20taking%20a%20whole%20slab%20away%20to%20be%20used%20as%20weapons.%20Some%20men%20went%20inside%20an%20old%20house%20and%20demolished%20a%20broken%20wall%20for%20more%20arsenal%20to%20attack%20the%20marauding%20enemy.%20Apart%20from%20this%20advantage%2C%20we%20were%20also%20at%20a%20height.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20Hindu%20mob%20tried%20to%20push%20up%20the%20slope%2C%20they%20were%20easily%20turned%20back.%20%E2%80%98I%20will%20return%20and%20fuck%20your%20mother%20in%20front%20of%20you%2C%E2%80%99%20cried%20one%20of%20them%20as%20a%20part%20of%20a%20brick%20hit%20his%20head%20and%20blood%20gushed%20down%20his%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20minutes%20later%2C%20they%20returned%20with%20more%20guns%2C%20and%20all%20our%20advantages%20turned%20to%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInside%20our%20home%2C%20my%20mother%20was%20trying%20to%20decide%20whether%20it%20was%20time%20to%20run.%20She%20was%20reading%20%3Cem%3EAyatul%20Kursi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20verse%20Muslims%20read%20when%20they%20are%20afraid.%20My%20father%20was%20at%20his%20office%20at%20the%20university%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20town.%20Mother%20told%20my%20elder%20brother%2C%20Saad%2C%20to%20keep%20a%20watch%20and%20gauge%20the%20danger%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20back%20in%20a%20rush.%20%E2%80%98Ammi%2C%20bullets%20are%20being%20fired%20from%20everywhere.%20One%20missed%20my%20ear%20by%20a%20few%20inches%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said%2C%20sounding%20more%20excited%20than%20afraid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Did%20it%20really%20go%20past%20your%20ear%3F%20Don%E2%80%99t%20lie%2C%E2%80%99%20I%20asked%20circumspectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20could%20answer%2C%20Sayema%2C%20our%20sister%2C%20began%20to%20cry.%20She%20had%20been%20calling%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20office%20landline%20from%20her%20Nokia%201100%20phone%20non-stop.%20Her%20husband%20had%20given%20her%20this%20brand-new%20phone%20with%20an%20orange%20keypad%20before%20she%20left%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20come%20home%20to%20deliver%20their%20first%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20eight-month-old%20baby%20in%20Sayema%E2%80%99s%20belly%20was%20our%20primary%20concern.%20Running%20away%20involved%20the%20risk%20that%20she%20%E2%80%93%20or%20anyone%20else%20among%20us%20%E2%80%93%20could%20be%20shot.%20Or%20Hindus%20could%20enter%20our%20house%20through%20the%20garage%20door%20and%20set%20it%20on%20fire%20(like%20they%20once%20had%20when%20Sayema%20was%20one).%20As%20my%20mother%20weighed%20her%20options%2C%20four%20strange%20men%20rushed%20into%20our%20home.%20%E2%80%98Baaji%2C%20we%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20terrace%20to%20attack%20enemies%20from%20a%20height.%20Unlock%20your%20staircase%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20the%20shortest%20among%20them%2C%20his%20eyes%20wet%20with%20tears%20of%20anger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Forgive%20us%2C%20for%20Allah%E2%80%99s%20sake!%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20our%20home%20used%20for%20rioting%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20my%20mother%20as%20she%20pushed%20them%20out%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98We%20are%20fighting%20to%20save%20you.%20If%20not%20for%20us%2C%20they%E2%80%99d%20have%20entered%20your%20homes%20by%20now%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said%20before%20going%20away%20to%20knock%20on%20other%20doors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20latched%20our%20door%2C%20I%20heard%20the%20sound%20of%20stones%20hitting%20the%20ground.%20It%20was%20coming%20from%20across%20the%20foyer%20in%20Palle%20Ghar%2C%20the%20portion%20of%20our%20ancestral%20home%20inhabited%20by%20the%20twenty-one%20members%20of%20my%20paternal%20aunt%E2%80%99s%20family.%20The%20attack%20had%20arrived%20there.%20I%20saw%20bricks%20raining%20down%20her%20porch%2C%20bypassing%20the%20giant%20peepal%20tree%20separating%20her%20home%20from%20Hindu%20neighbours.%20%E2%80%98I%20have%20spent%20my%20whole%20life%20here%20but%20%3Cem%3Enever%20%3C%2Fem%3Eseen%20such%20bad%20times%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20Mehro%2C%20my%20Phuppo%2C%20blankness%20reigning%20in%20her%20green%20eyes.%20Her%20sons%20had%20moved%20their%20children%20to%20safe%20places%2C%20far%20away%20from%20bricks%20and%20bullets.%20Two%20of%20the%20sons%20and%20their%20families%20would%20leave%20this%20home%20in%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20attack%20on%20Palle%20Ghar%20had%20also%20opened%20up%20another%20grim%20possibility%3A%20people%20firing%20bullets%20at%20our%20house.%20%E2%80%98The%20Hindus%20are%20standing%20with%20guns%20on%20their%20terrace.%20I%20saw%20somebody%20firing%20from%20the%20roof%20of%20Punjab%20Bank%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20Nadim%20Bhai%2C%20Phuppo%E2%80%99s%20youngest%20son.%20Anyone%20standing%20on%20their%20terrace%20now%20scared%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Ammi%2C%20should%20I%20close%20the%20window%3F%20They%20can%20see%20us%20moving%20inside%20our%20house%2C%E2%80%99%20I%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20act%20too%20smart.%20Stay%20away%20from%20the%20windows%2C%E2%80%99%20she%20said%2C%20reciting%20another%20set%20of%20%3Cem%3Edua%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20the%20women%20of%20Palle%20Ghar.%20I%20shut%20the%20window.%20I%20wanted%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20seeing%20us%20moving%20around%20our%20living%20room.%20My%20brother%20promptly%20switched%20off%20the%20lights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20Tariq%20Bhai%2C%20my%20paternal%20cousin%2C%20came%20rushing%20into%20our%20living%20room.%20%E2%80%98They%20are%20trying%20to%20climb%20up.%20You%20should%20run%20across%20the%20lane%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98What%20about%20Sayema%3F%E2%80%99%20Ammi%20asked%2C%20pointing%20to%20my%20sister%E2%80%99s%20eight-month-old%20stomach%20bulge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Let%E2%80%99s%20walk%20slowly%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20Saad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20all%20the%20panic%2C%20Ammi%20took%20her%20time%20to%20lock%20the%20doors%20and%20hide%20anything%20that%20had%20a%20remote%20chance%20of%20being%20stolen.%20Finally%2C%20we%20left%20our%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%2C%20the%20screams%20of%20women%20mingled%20with%20gunshots%2C%20profanity%20and%20religious%20slogans%20to%20create%20a%20strange%20cacophony%20of%20chaos.%20We%20walked%20holding%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20hands%20before%20running%20into%20a%20narrow%20lane%20that%20led%20towards%20Jama%20Masjid.%20%E2%80%98This%20way!%20This%20way!%E2%80%99%20said%20neighbourhood%20women%20we%20had%20never%20met%2C%20showing%20us%20the%20way%20to%20run%20away%20from%20our%20home%20while%20they%20were%20firmly%20planted%20in%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20left%2C%20the%20four%20strangers%20who%20wanted%20to%20enter%20our%20terrace%20returned%20to%20our%20home.%20They%20broke%20the%20rusty%20lock%20on%20the%20staircase.%20One%20of%20them%20later%20died%20of%20a%20bullet%20wound%20in%20a%20clinic%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20later%20that%20I%20found%20out%20that%20Shadab%20had%20also%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EZeyad%20Masroor%20Khan%20is%20a%20journalist%2C%20writer%20and%20documentary%20film-maker%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%20his%20decade-long%20journalistic%20career%2C%20he%20has%20worked%20with%20national%20and%20international%20media%20companies%20like%20%3C%2Fem%3EReuters%2C%20Vice%2C%20Brut%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20Deccan%20Herald.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700794895000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24082915%2F339836345_6ec5c293e6_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcity-of-fire-book-growing-up-as-muslim-aligarh-babri-riots%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'City%20on%20Fire'%20is%20a%20rare%20visceral%20portrait%20of%20how%20everyday%20violence%20and%20hate%20become%20a%20part%20of%20our%20lives%20and%20consciousness%3B%20a%20society%20where%20name%20and%20clothes%20mark%20out%20a%20person%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98other%E2%80%99.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcity-of-fire-book-growing-up-as-muslim-aligarh-babri-riots%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Understanding%20the%20Context%20and%20Concerns%20Over%20North%20Korea's%20'Spy%20Satellite%20Launch'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184734%2FScreenshot-2023-11-23-at-6.45.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%20North%20Korea%20appears%20to%20have%20successfully%20launched%20a%20spy%20satellite%20into%20space.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20two%20attempts%20to%20put%20its%20first%20military%20reconnaissance%20satellite%20in%20orbit%20had%20failed.%20For%20North%20Korea%2C%20this%20is%20a%20much-desired%20success.%20The%20earlier%20attempts%20had%20taken%20place%20during%20May%20and%20August.%20The%20way%20North%20Korea%20handled%20these%20recent%20failures%20and%20continued%20to%20work%20towards%20success%20indicates%20maturity%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20and%20political%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20Korean%20state%20was%20unusually%20honest%20in%20accepting%20its%20recent%20failures.%20No%20false%20claims%20about%20the%20success%20were%20made%2C%20and%20neither%20was%20the%20world%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20to%20guess%20about%20its%20intentions.%20There%20were%20no%20attempts%20of%20any%20false%20self-glorification.%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20may%20have%20realised%20that%20the%20process%20of%20technology%20development%20is%20difficult%20and%20requires%20patience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20appears%20to%20have%20understood%20that%20to%20leap%20into%20the%20space%20domain%2C%20outside%20assistance%20is%20required.%20Between%20September%2012%20and%2017%2C%20Kim%20made%20an%20official%20visit%20to%20Russia.%20One%20of%20the%20meetings%20between%20him%20and%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20was%20at%20the%20Vostochny%20Cosmodrome%2C%20a%20Russian%20spaceport.%20There%20is%20both%20symbolic%20and%20strategic%20significance%20to%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20location%20and%20leads%20one%20to%20ask%20if%20the%20recent%20spy%20satellite%20success%20was%20assisted%20by%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184147%2FKim_Jong-un_and_Vladimir_Putin_2023-09-13_01-300x153.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686137%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKim%20Jong-un%20and%20Vladimir%20Putin%20before%20visiting%20the%20Vostochny%20Cosmodrome.%20Photo%3A%20Kremlin.ru%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%20of%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20space%20programme%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20along%20with%20Iran%2C%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20using%20their%20space%20programmes%20for%20signalling%20their%20missile%20capabilities.%20However%2C%20the%20way%20in%20which%20North%20Korea%20has%20been%20undertaking%20missile%20testing%20during%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20it%20is%20obvious%20that%20it%20does%20not%20require%20any%20such%20smokescreen.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20judge%20the%20North%20Korean%20space%20programme%20on%20its%20merit%20and%20the%20actual%20rationale%20behind%20such%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%204%2C%201998%2C%20the%20North%20Korean%20authorities%20claimed%20the%20successful%20launch%20of%20their%20first%20artificial%20satellite%2C%20Kwangmyongsong-1%20(Brightstar-1).%20Experts%2C%20at%20that%20time%2C%20had%20opined%20that%20the%20mission%20was%20not%20a%20success.%20North%20Korea%20is%20known%20to%20have%20achieved%20success%20in%20putting%20the%20satellite%20into%20orbit%20in%20its%20fourth%20attempt%20on%20December%201%2C%202012%2C%20and%20this%20success%20earned%20it%20the%20tag%20of%20spacefaring%20state.%20In%202016%2C%20North%20Korea%20successfully%20launched%20Kwangmyongsong-4%20into%20the%20Low%20Earth%20Orbit%20or%20LEO%20(payload%20could%20be%20around%20200%20kg).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Democratic%20People%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20of%20Korea%20(DPRK)%E2%80%99s%20space%20programme%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20an%20expansion%20of%20its%20missile%20programme.%20The%20Korean%20Committee%20of%20Space%20Technology%20(KCST)%20was%20established%20sometime%20during%20the%201980s.%20This%20agency%20was%20responsible%20for%20research%2C%20satellite%20manufacture%20and%20launching%2C%20and%20managing%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20rocket%20launch%20sites.%20Subsequently%2C%20on%20April%201%2C%202013%2C%20the%20National%20Aerospace%20Development%20Administration%20(NADA)%20was%20established%2C%20which%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20DPRK%E2%80%99s%20central%20institution%20to%20organise%20all%20space%20development%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20time%20now%2C%20North%20Korea%20has%20been%20focusing%20its%20efforts%20on%20expanding%20in%20the%20space%20domain%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20military-relevant%20applications.%20In%202017%2C%20it%20announced%20a%20five-year%20plan%20to%20conquer%20space.%20As%20per%20this%2C%20it%20had%20a%20plan%20in%20place%20for%20building%20a%20satellite%20communication%20system%20by%20June%202019.%20However%2C%20this%20has%20not%20happened%20so%20far%20and%20nothing%20much%20is%20known%20in%20this%20regard.%20During%20a%20party%20congress%20(January%202021)%2C%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20mentioned%20the%20proposal%20for%20developing%20military%20reconnaissance%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2031%2C%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20first%20attempt%20to%20put%20its%20first%20spy%20satellite%20into%20space%20failed.%20This%20mission%20involved%20the%20launching%20of%20the%20Malligyong-1%20satellite%20by%20using%20the%20newly%20developed%20Chollima-1%20rocket.%20As%20per%20North%20Korea%E2%80%99s%20news%20agency%2C%20the%20failure%20resulted%20from%20the%20low%20reliability%20of%20the%20new%20engine%20system%20used%20on%20the%20Chollima-1%20rocket%20and%20the%20unstable%20character%20of%20the%20fuel.%20The%20second%20launch%20undertaken%20on%20August%2024%20failed%20during%20the%20third%20stage%20of%20its%20flight.%20The%20state%20agency%20was%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20the%20failure%20was%20due%20to%20an%20error%20in%20the%20emergency%20blasting%20system%20during%20the%20third-stage%20flight%20and%20the%20issue%20was%20rectifiable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImplications%20for%20the%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20is%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20state.%20It%20is%20advocating%20its%20nuclear%20and%20missile%20programmes%20as%20formidable%20pillars%20of%20its%20security%20architecture.%20Now%20space%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20new%20pillar%20in%20this%20structure.%20Having%20operational%20spy%20satellites%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20improves%20the%20%E2%80%98worth%E2%80%99%20of%20DPRK%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20deterrence%20mechanism.%20Pyongyang%20is%20open%20about%20its%20space%20ambitions%20and%20argues%20that%20it%20has%20a%20%E2%80%98sovereign%20right%E2%80%99%20to%20develop%20spy%20satellites%20to%20address%20its%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20the%20United%20States%20and%20South%20Korean%20administrations%20are%20not%20found%20working%20towards%20any%20possible%20inter-Korean%20rapprochement.%20Together%20with%20Japan%2C%20they%20condemned%20the%20launch%2C%20which%2C%20according%20to%20them%2C%20used%20ballistic%20missile%20technology%20in%20violation%20of%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20high%20time%20for%20them%20to%20realise%20that%20old%20ideas%20of%20sanctions%2C%20arms%2C%20and%20export%20control%20measures%20and%20undertaking%20military%20exercises%20in%20Korean%20waters%20actually%20mean%20nothing%20to%20a%20state%20like%20North%20Korea%2C%20which%20is%20so%20brazen%20in%20its%20approach.%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20understands%20what%20such%20powers%20have%20done%20to%20Colonel%20Gaddafi%20and%20Saddam%20Hussein.%20He%20is%20not%20keen%20on%20any%20reconciliation%20from%20the%20position%20of%20weakness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20war%20and%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20military%20needs%20for%20artillery%20shells%20and%20other%20munitions%20are%20drawing%20North%20Korea%20closer%20to%20Russia.%20In%20future%2C%20Russia-DPRK-China%20nexus%20is%20likely%20to%20emerge%20as%20a%20major%20nuisance%20for%20the%20US.%20It%20is%20important%20for%20the%20US%20to%20realise%20that%20taking%20a%20maximalist%20position%20against%20North%20Korea%20(that%20they%20should%20denuclearise)%20is%20not%20going%20to%20help.%C2%A0They%20need%20to%20start%20a%20process%20of%20constructive%20engagement.%20Possibly%2C%20space%20technologies%20could%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98low-hanging%20fruit%E2%80%99%20in%20this%20regard.%20These%20technologies%20are%20dual-use%20technologies%20with%20significant%20civilian%20utility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20North%20Korea%20needs%20greater%20assistance%20for%20socioeconomic%20development.%20Could%20the%20US%20think%20of%20using%20space%20technologies%20as%20an%20option%20in%20this%20regard%3F%20Some%20%E2%80%98outside%20the%20box%E2%80%99%20thinking%20is%20required%20to%20address%20the%20North%20Korean%20conundrums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700793026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23184734%2FScreenshot-2023-11-23-at-6.45.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fcontext-concerns-north-koreas-spy-satellite-launch%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20Japan%20condemned%20the%20launch%2C%20accusing%20Pyongyang%20of%20using%20ballistic%20missile%20technology%20in%20violation%20of%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions.%20Can%20such%20a%20maximalist%20position%20against%20North%20Korea%20yield%20anything%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fcontext-concerns-north-koreas-spy-satellite-launch%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Income%20Tax%20Data%20Reveals%20That%20Increase%20in%20Compliance%20Is%20Marginal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01171239%2Findian-rupee-money-cash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%20(CBDT)%20has%20released%20data%20on%20income%20tax%20payees%20for%20financial%20years%202013-14%20to%202022-23.%20More%20detailed%20data%20about%20different%20categories%20of%20tax%20payees%20are%20available%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202020-21.%20This%20data%20can%20be%20used%20to%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%20of%20the%20top%20income%20earners%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFew%20direct%20tax%20payers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncome%20tax%20is%20paid%20by%20a%20minuscule%20percent%20of%20the%20population.%20Official%20data%20shows%20that%207.4%20crore%20individuals%20filed%20tax%20returns%20in%20FY2022-23%20and%206.75%20crore%20in%20FY2020-21.%20In%20this%20earlier%20year%2C%20there%20were%20also%202.1%20crore%20people%20who%20did%20not%20file%20a%20tax%20return%20but%20paid%20Tax%20Deducted%20at%20Source%20(TDS).%20So%2C%20in%20FY2020-21%2C%20effectively%20there%20were%208.85%20crore%20people%20in%20the%20tax%20net%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%206.6%25%20of%20the%20population.%20Since%20we%20do%20not%20have%20corresponding%20data%20on%20those%20not%20filing%20tax%20return%20but%20paying%20TDS%20for%20FY%202022-23%2C%20we%20do%20not%20yet%20know%20the%20total%20number%20of%20entities%20in%20the%20tax%20net%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20paying%20income%20tax%20or%20filing%20a%20tax%20return%20has%20to%20have%20an%20income%20above%20the%20income%20tax%20exemption%20limit%20and%20therefore%20has%20to%20be%20among%20the%20top%20income%20earners%20in%20the%20country.%20What%20is%20their%20distribution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exemption%20limit%20for%20determining%20tax%20liability%20is%20now%20Rs%203%20lakh%20but%20has%20been%20Rs%202.5%20lakh%2C%20with%20some%20concessions%20for%20senior%20and%20super%20senior%20citizens.%20With%20a%20standard%20deduction%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20and%20rebate%20under%20Section%2087A%2C%20till%20now%20an%20individual%20did%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20any%20tax%20up%20to%20a%20taxable%20income%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh.%20Of%20India%E2%80%99s%20per%20capita%20annual%20income%20at%20current%20prices%20of%20Rs%201%2C50%2C007%20in%202021-22%2C%20this%20is%20333%25.%20From%20the%20current%20financial%20year%2C%20tax%20will%20have%20to%20be%20paid%20at%20income%20of%20above%20Rs%207.5%25%2C%20414%25%20of%20the%20likely%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20about%20Rs%201%2C81%2C000.%20So%20those%20in%20the%20tax%20net%20are%20in%20the%20tail%20of%20the%20income%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20much%20concession%2C%20for%20FY2020-21%2C%20out%20of%206.76%20crore%20e-returns%20filed%2C%204.46%20crore%20paid%20nil%20tax%20(67.3%25%20of%20the%20total).%20The%202.1%20crore%20who%20did%20not%20file%20a%20return%20but%20paid%20TDS%20must%20have%20had%20an%20income%20below%20Rs%202.5%20lakh%2C%20otherwise%20they%20would%20have%20had%20to%20file%20a%20return.%20Adding%20these%20two%20numbers%2C%20effectively%2C%206.6%20crore%20returns%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%208.85%20crore%20(73.4%25)%20were%20filed%20by%20those%20with%20low%20incomes.%2091%20lakh%20(10.3%25%20of%20those%20in%20the%20tax%20net)%20had%20taxable%20incomes%20above%20Rs%209.5%20lakh%20and%20who%20can%20be%20called%20well-off%20in%20the%20Indian%20context.%20About%202.15%20lakh%20declared%20income%20above%20Rs%201%20crore%20and%20maybe%20characterised%20as%20wealthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20brief%2C%20people%20in%20top%20rung%20of%20the%20income%20ladder%20in%20the%20country%20were%20those%20who%20were%20in%20the%20income%20tax%20net%20(6.6%25%20of%20the%20population)%20even%20if%20they%20did%20not%20pay%20income%20tax.%20Out%20of%20these%2C%20only%200.68%25%20of%20the%20population%20were%20the%20really%20well%20off%20who%20effectively%20paid%20income%20tax.%20Further%2C%200.016%25%20declared%20an%20income%20above%20Rs%201%20crore%20and%20had%20a%20share%20of%2038.6%25%20of%20the%20taxable%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECaveats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20picture%20of%20the%20well-off%2C%20characterised%20by%20those%20who%20effectively%20pay%20income%20tax%2C%20is%20incomplete.%20Two%20additional%20factors%20need%20to%20be%20taken%20into%20account.%20First%2C%20the%20rich%20families%20split%20up%20their%20incomes.%20This%20enables%20them%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20concessions%20on%20each%20of%20the%20returns%20filed%20and%20each%20of%20the%20incomes%20may%20then%20fall%20in%20the%20lower%20income%20bracket%20on%20which%20a%20lower%20tax%20rate%20may%20apply.%20Second%2C%20the%20well-off%20resort%20to%20black%20income%20generation%20by%20not%20declaring%20their%20true%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20point%20implies%20that%20the%200.68%25%20people%20who%20paid%20significant%20amounts%20of%20income%20tax%20belong%20to%20an%20even%20smaller%20percent%20of%20the%20families.%20So%2C%20the%20actual%20family%20income%20of%20the%20well-off%20is%20much%20higher.%20Since%20the%20poor%20face%20unemployment%2C%20under%20employment%20and%20joblessness%2C%20their%20family%20income%20is%20not%20much%20higher%20than%20what%20a%20poor%20individual%20earns.%20The%20implication%20is%20that%20the%20gap%20in%20family%20incomes%20between%20the%20well-off%20and%20the%20poor%20would%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20much%20larger%20than%20gap%20in%20incomes%20shown%20by%20the%20data%20on%20individuals%20paying%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20black%20incomes%20are%20generated%20by%20the%20well-off%2C%20who%20have%20substantial%20incomes.%20Those%20who%20have%20an%20income%20below%20the%20taxable%20limit%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20hide%20their%20income.%20They%20do%20not%20have%20to%20file%20a%20return%20or%20declare%20their%20income%20to%20the%20tax%20authorities.%20Those%20who%20have%20a%20taxable%20income%20of%2C%20say%2C%20up%20to%20Rs%209.5%20lakh%2C%20need%20pay%20only%20a%20few%20percent%20of%20it%20as%20tax%2C%20if%20they%20take%20advantage%20of%20deductions%20under%2080C%2C%2080D%2C%2080TTA%2C%20etc.%20So%20they%20will%20hardly%20benefit%20from%20hiding%20their%20income%20and%20will%20not%20be%20generators%20of%20black%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20well-off%2C%20especially%20businessmen%20and%20professionals%20who%20declare%20a%20lower%20income%20to%20tax%20authorities%20so%20as%20to%20pay%20a%20smaller%20portion%20of%20their%20income%20as%20tax.%20Some%20of%20them%20completely%20escape%20the%20tax%20net%20by%20not%20filing%20a%20return%20or%20by%20showing%20an%20income%20below%20the%20taxable%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20factors%20lead%20to%20the%20official%20data%20underestimating%20the%20skewedness%20of%20income%20distribution%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHas%20compliance%20increased%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organised%20sector%20has%20higher%20incomes%20and%20contributes%20most%20to%20direct%20taxes.%20It%20produces%2055%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20Its%20share%20of%20GDP%20would%20have%20risen%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20disproportionately%20hit%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%20The%20GDP%20was%20Rs%201%2C98%2C00%2C914%20crore%20in%20FY%202020-21%2C%20the%20Covid%20year.%20So%2C%20Rs%201%2C08%2C90%2C000%20crore%20should%20have%20been%20captured%20in%20the%20tax%20net%20from%20the%20organised%20sector.%20Some%20more%20should%20have%20come%20from%20the%20few%20well-off%20businesses%20in%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetailed%20data%20for%20FY%202020-21%20shows%20that%20the%20taxable%20income%20declared%20by%20all%20return%20filers%20was%20Rs%2069%2C59%2C552.48%20crore.%20This%20is%20about%2035.15%25%20of%20the%20GDP%20and%20about%2063.9%25%20of%20what%20should%20have%20been%20shown%20as%20declared%20incomes%20by%20the%20organised%20sector.%20On%20this%20declared%20income%2C%20the%20tax%20collected%20was%20Rs%209%2C47%2C176%20crore.%20The%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20was%20a%20very%20low%204.78%25.%20If%20black%20income%20generation%20were%20taken%20into%20account%2C%20it%20would%20be%20even%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20FY2021-22%2C%20GDP%20recovered%20from%20its%20low%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20became%20Rs%202%2C36%2C64%2C637%20crore.%20The%20direct%20tax%20collection%20increased%20to%20Rs%2014%2C12%2C422%20crore%2C%20so%20that%20the%20direct%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20rose%20to%205.97%25.%20In%202018-19%2C%20this%20figure%20was%20even%20higher%20at%206.02%25.%20But%2C%20even%20this%20figure%20is%20low%20compared%20to%20many%20developing%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20claims%20that%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20filing%20tax%20returns%20and%20presents%20this%20as%20an%20indication%20of%20better%20tax%20compliance%20and%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20black%20economy.%20According%20to%20the%20data%20just%20released%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20paying%20direct%20taxes%20has%20risen%20from%207%2C42%2C49%2C558%20in%20FY2016-17%20to%209%2C37%2C76%2C869%20in%20FY2021-22.%20This%20is%20impressive%2C%20but%20the%20catch%20is%20that%20most%20of%20the%20people%20entering%20the%20tax%20net%20declare%20nil%20income%20or%20a%20low%20income%2C%20as%20pointed%20out%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20reduction%20in%20black%20income%20generation%20would%20have%20meant%20that%20many%20more%20of%20the%20individuals%20with%20high%20incomes%20would%20have%20come%20into%20the%20tax%20net%2C%20and%20the%20direct%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20should%20have%20risen%20sharply%20instead%20of%20hovering%20between%205.5%25%20and%206%25%20since%202014-15.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20returns%20is%20due%20to%20the%20constancy%20of%20the%20income%20at%20which%20a%20tax%20return%20needs%20to%20be%20filed%20remaining%20unchanged%20at%20Rs%202.5%20lakh%2C%20while%20incomes%20have%20risen%20due%20to%20inflation.%20The%20per%20capita%20net%20national%20income%2C%20which%20tells%20us%20how%20much%20an%20average%20citizen%20is%20earning%2C%20is%2030.1%25%20higher%20in%202022-23%20than%20it%20was%20in%202019-20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20someone%20with%20an%20income%20of%20Rs%202%20lakh%20in%20FY2019-20%2C%20pre%20pandemic%2C%20would%20be%20earning%20Rs%202.6%20lakh%20in%20FY2022-23.%20In%202019-20%2C%20she%20would%20not%20have%20had%20to%20file%20a%20tax%20return%20while%20in%202022-23%20she%20would%20have%20to%20file%20a%20return.%20Thus%2C%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20return%20filers%20would%20automatically%20rise.%20But%20the%20tax%20they%20pay%20would%20not%20rise%2C%20so%20their%20entry%20into%20the%20tax%20net%20does%20not%20impact%20the%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20income%20tax%20data%20released%20recently%20points%20to%20the%20highly%20skewed%20nature%20of%20income%20distribution%20in%20the%20country%20with%20only%20about%200.68%25%20people%20paying%20effective%20taxes.%20The%20percentage%20of%20families%20they%20belong%20to%20would%20be%20even%20smaller.%20If%20tax%20manipulations%20by%20the%20wealthy%20and%20black%20income%20generation%20are%20taken%20into%20account%2C%20then%20the%20income%20distribution%20becomes%20even%20more%20skewed.%20Finally%2C%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20filers%20is%20due%20to%20inflation%20but%20this%20has%20hardly%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20direct%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20since%20most%20new%20entrants%20in%20the%20tax%20net%20file%20either%20nil%20return%20or%20are%20exempt%20from%20tax.%20So%2C%20tax%20compliance%20in%20the%20country%20has%20hardly%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArun%20Kumar%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EUnderstanding%20Black%20Economy%20and%20Black%20Money%20in%20India%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700789416000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01171239%2Findian-rupee-money-cash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fincome-tax-data-reveals-that-increase-in-compliance-is-marginal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20income%20tax%20data%20released%20recently%20points%20to%20the%20highly%20skewed%20nature%20of%20income%20distribution%20in%20the%20country%2C%20with%20only%20about%200.68%25%20people%20paying%20effective%20taxes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fincome-tax-data-reveals-that-increase